                        <rdg source="#bertolini1875a #bertolini1875b">aperire</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="3" from="#w3" to="w3">
                        <lem><expan><abbr>v<choice><corr>o</corr><sic>q</sic></choice>lu</abbr><ex>erit</ex></expan></lem>
                        <rdg source="#bertolini1875a #bertolini1875b #cilv8758 #ilcv506 #holder"><expan><abbr>volu</abbr><ex>erit</ex></expan></rdg>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#roveos" xml:lang="la">Flavius Roveos</persName>, <term xml:lang="la">centenarius</term> of the <term xml:lang="la">numerus</term> of <term xml:lang="la">comitatenses seniores</term> horse-archers, set up this sarcophagus for himself at his own expense.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If anyone should wish to open it, he shall pay five (roman) pounds of silver to the <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term>.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#roveos" xml:lang="la">Flavius Roveos</persName>, <term xml:lang="la">centenarius</term> del <term xml:lang="la">numerus</term> degli <term xml:lang="la">equites sagittarii seniores</term> comitatensi, pose a proprie spese (questa) arca per sé.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Se qualcuno vorrà aprirla, verserà alle casse del <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term> cinque libbre (romane) d'argento.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p><persName ref="#roveos" xml:lang="la">Flavius Roveos</persName> was the <term xml:lang="la">centenarius</term> of a <term xml:lang="la">numerus</term> of horse-archers, the <term xml:lang="la">equites sagittarii seniores</term>, recorded in the <title xml:lang="la">Notitia Dignitatum</title> (Not. dign, occ. VI, 43; VII, 159). It appears that the <term xml:lang="la">equites sagittarii</term>, along with other cavalry units, were originally part of the emperor's elite guard during the time of Gallienus, before being deployed to garrison the Danubian and Eastern provinces starting from the reign of Aurelian (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#rocco2012">Rocco 2012, 87</ref>).</p>
                <p>The <term xml:lang="la">cognomen</term> <persName type="cognomen" xml:lang="la">Roveos</persName> has Celtic origins according to Holder (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#holder1904">Holder 1904, 1236</ref>).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="it">
                <p><persName ref="#roveos" xml:lang="la">Flavius Roveos</persName> era il <term xml:lang="la">centenarius</term> di un <term xml:lang="la">numerus</term> di arcieri a cavallo, gli <term xml:lang="la">equites sagittarii seniores</term>, attestati nella <title xml:lang="la">Notitia Dignitatum</title> (Not. dign, occ. VI, 43; VII, 159). Sembra che inizialmente gli <term xml:lang="la">equites sagittarii</term>, assieme ad altri reparti di cavalleria, facessero parte della guardia dell'élite dell'imperatore ai tempi di Gallieno, per poi essere dislocati a presidio delle province danubiane e orientali a partire dal regno di Aureliano (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#rocco2012">Rocco 2012, 87</ref>).</p>
                <p>Il <term xml:lang="la">cognomen</term> <persName type="cognomen" xml:lang="la">Roveos</persName> ha origini celtiche secondo Holder (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#holder">Holder 1904, 1236</ref>).</p>
            </div>
